		"description": "<p>Comrades occasionally require a bit more than just the knowledge that their allies have their backs in a fight; some blood sharing can go a long way towards solidifying those bonds.</p><p>With an Action, a creature ties an end of this short, scarlet colored strap around a willing creatureâ€™s appendage and the other end around themself, becoming a donor. The donor may give any number of their own remaining hit dice to an ally; the donor must have a higher hit die size than the recipient. If the donor has a smaller hit die size than the recipient, they may still donate, but the process requires 2 hit dice donated per 1 hit die received by the willing creature.</p><p>Once used, the Blood-Bond Band crumbles into a powder resembling dried blood and can no longer be used. </p>",
